               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-320" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-320" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-320" type="surname" value="SMALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-320" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SMALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am master of a brig in St. Katherine's Docks. About half-past five o'clock on 27th June I missed my watch—this is it—(<hi rend="italic">pro<lb></lb>duced</hi>)—I had seen it safe three hours before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-321" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-321" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-321" type="surname" value="GILES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-321" type="given" value="SHEPHERD"></interp>SHEPHERD GILES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am mate of the vessel. I saw the prisoner on board about twelve o'clock that day—I saw the watch in the cabin, and saw him go down and come up again.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> He dined on board with you?</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184808210030"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he had been there with me several times—I was with him until we went to Astley's, at night, except about ten minutes, when he left me in Aldgate, saying he was going to see a friend to <hi rend="italic">raise the wind</hi>—it was then half-past five.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-322" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-322" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-322" type="surname" value="DELBRIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-322" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN DELBRIDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker's man—I produce a watch pawned between five and six o'clock on 27th June, by the prisoner, I believe.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
